---
const points = [
  ['GalexC', 'Operator-owned environment'],
  ['Claude Code', 'Interactive coding harness'],
  ['Hermes', 'Flexible agentic autonomy'],
  ['OpenClaw', 'Open autonomy-forward stack'],
];

const cards = [
  ['GalexC', 'Best understood as a personal operating environment for shaping, dispatch, review, and durable memory.'],
  ['Claude Code', 'Best understood as a powerful coding harness centered on an active repo session.'],
  ['Hermes', 'Optimizes for flexible skill-driven behavior and broader agentic autonomy.'],
  ['OpenClaw', 'Represents a more open, hackable, autonomy-forward posture.'],
];

const workflow = [
  ['Shape', 'Define the work before anything runs.'],
  ['Dispatch', 'Send only what is bounded enough to trust.'],
  ['Review', 'Return through a PR or artifact with receipts.'],
  ['Keep', 'Store the useful result as durable context.'],
];
---

<div class="essay-page comparison-page">
  <section class="page-hero-note-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Comparisons</p>
      <h1 class="page-display-title">Where GalexC sits in the agent landscape.</h1>
      <p class="page-lede">
        GalexC overlaps with coding agents, autonomous harnesses, and other emerging
        AI systems, but it is not trying to be a generic assistant or a pure autonomy
        play. The point is a durable personal operating environment: operator-owned,
        reviewable, and built for real ongoing work.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="page-module page-module-panel compact-callout">
      <p class="eyebrow">Not a scorecard</p>
      <p>Center of gravity, not rankings.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-module page-module-panel axes-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Landscape axes</p>
    <div class="axes-card__frame">
      <div class="axes-card__x"></div>
      <div class="axes-card__y"></div>
      <p class="axes-card__axis-label axes-card__axis-label-x-start">single-session coding tool</p>
      <p class="axes-card__axis-label axes-card__axis-label-x-end">durable operating environment</p>
      <p class="axes-card__axis-label axes-card__axis-label-y-start">high-delegation autonomy</p>
      <p class="axes-card__axis-label axes-card__axis-label-y-end">operator-steered bounded execution</p>
      {
        points.map(([label, note], index) => (
          <div class:list={['axes-card__point', `axes-card__point-${index + 1}`]}>
            <strong>{label}</strong>
            <span>{note}</span>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
    <p class="page-caption">
      Left to right: single-session coding tool to durable operating environment.
      Bottom to top: high-delegation autonomy to operator-steered bounded execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="comparison-cards">
    {
      cards.map(([title, body]) => (
        <article class="page-module page-module-panel comparison-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">Reference point</p>
          <h2>{title}</h2>
          <p>{body}</p>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </section>

  <section class="page-module page-module-panel comparison-workflow-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workflow shape</p>
    <div class="comparison-workflow-list">
      {
        workflow.map(([title, body]) => (
          <div class="comparison-workflow-list__item">
            <strong>{title}</strong>
            <p>{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-grid-two">
    <article class="page-module page-module-panel boundary-split">
      <p class="eyebrow">What GalexC is not</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Not just a chat shell with extra tools</li>
        <li>Not a generic SaaS copilot</li>
        <li>Not an agents-gone-wild framework</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="page-module">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why the distinction matters</p>
      <p>
        If you want the fastest path to one interactive coding loop, other tools may be
        a more natural fit. If you want an operator-owned environment for shaping,
        execution, memory, and review, GalexC is aiming at that territory on purpose.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</div>
